  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (software-fault gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The solver pipeline integrates a proprietary finite-volume CFD kernel, a Python-based hemolysis post-processor implementing the Giersiepen–Wurzinger power-law model, and an MPI-parallel mesh partitioner. All validation runs are reported as completing nominally; no software-fault stress testing (convergence-failure injection, NaN-propagation checks, or parallel race-condition probes) was performed or documented.",
