      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence study — nominal completion",
      "description": "Three mesh densities (coarse 1.2 M cells, medium 3.8 M cells, fine 9.1 M cells) were evaluated at the 3 L/min / 3000 RPM operating point. Grid convergence index (GCI) computed for wall shear stress and hemolysis index. All three runs completed without solver interruption. GCI for hemolysis index between medium and fine meshes: 2.3%. Medium mesh selected for production runs. No solver divergence, NaN fields, or abnormal termination events were observed or deliberately induced during this study.",
      "quantitativeOutcome": "GCI_hemolysis = 2.3%; GCI_WSS = 1.8%; all runs nominal"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-02-experimental-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental hemolysis comparison — five operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at five flow-speed combinations: (2 L/min, 2500 RPM), (3 L/min, 3000 RPM), (4 L/min, 3000 RPM), (5 L/min, 3500 RPM), (6 L/min, 4000 RPM). All simulations ran to convergence (residuals < 1e-5) under standard operating inputs. Relative error ranged from 4.1% to 11.7%. RH < 1 criterion satisfied at all points. Post-processing Python scripts executed without exception. Parallel MPI runs (16 ranks) completed nominally across all cases.",
      "quantitativeOutcome": "Max relative error 11.7%; RH < 1 at all 5 operating points; all runs nominal completion"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-03-tolerance-sensitivity",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Geometric tolerance sensitivity — dimensional variation sweep",
      "description": "Fourteen geometric variants (±tolerances on impeller blade clearance, volute gap, and inlet radius) simulated to identify worst-case hemolysis configuration. All 14 runs completed nominally. Maximum NIH increase relative to nominal geometry: 18.4% at maximum blade clearance condition, remaining below the RH < 1 acceptance threshold when compared to predicate device. A single run at the tightest blade clearance (variant G-03) was restarted after an early divergence at iteration 120; the restart from iteration 100 completed normally and the final result was used. This isolated restart event was attributed to an aggressive initial time-step and was not further investigated as a software fault mode.",
      "quantitativeOutcome": "14/14 variants completed; worst-case NIH delta +18.4%; RH_max = 0.87 < 1.0"
    },
