    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for Model Risk Level 2. The CFD model predicts NIH within 11.7% of experimental measurements across five operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Mesh discretization error (GCI 2.3%) is within the 5% threshold. SQA documentation is in place for both the commercial solver and the in-house post-processor. The isolated solver divergence in variant G-03 was resolved by restart and does not affect the validity of the production dataset. The six not-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per the ASME V&V 40 framework. The model is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the COU decision regarding worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
